<subSubSection id="C3196502CB7FBD71EFBB01C3FE82FDEF" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC3689CB7FBD71EFBB01C3FE82FDEF" blockId="1.[151,1436,430,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EFBB01C3FEFBFE7F" bold="true" box="[151,273,430,455]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D0ACB7FBD71ED6301C3FD5CFE7F" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[591,694,430,455]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71ED6301C3FD5CFE7F" box="[591,694,430,455]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Porcellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed by the enlarged pleon-epimera constituting continuous outline with the pereon; pereon-epimera I with cocave posterolateral margins; head with welldeveloped lateral lobes; eyes with more than 20 ommatidia; telson triangular with concave lateral margins; pleopod exopodites I–II with monospiracular covered lungs and no conglobation ability (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B78CB7FBD71EB630277FA72FD8B" author="Schmalfuss" box="[1103,1432,538,563]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" refString="Schmalfuss, H. &amp; Ferrara, F. (1978) Terrestrial isopods from West Africa, Part 2: Families Tylidae, Ligiidae, Trichoniscidae, Styloniscidae, Rhyscotidae, Halophilosciidae, Philosciidae, Platyarthridae, Rhyscotidae, Trachelipidae, Porcellionidae, Armadillidiidae. Monitore zoologico italiano, Nuova Serie, Supplemento, 11, 15 - 97." type="journal article" year="1978">Schmalfuss &amp; Ferrara 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B78CB7FBD71EFBB0253FEB6FDEF" author="Schmalfuss" box="[151,348,574,599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" refString="Schmalfuss, H. (1992) The terrestrial isopod genus Porcellio in western Asia (Oniscidea: Porcellionidae). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A, 475, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="1992">Schmalfuss 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3196502CB7FBD71EFEB020FFE1CFCCF" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBC3689CB7FBD71EFEB020FFE1CFCCF" blockId="1.[151,1436,430,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EFEB020FFED1FDC3" bold="true" box="[199,315,610,635]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D0ACB7FBD71EE90020FFDC9FDC3" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[444,547,610,635]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EE90020FFDC9FDC3" box="[444,547,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Porcellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large taxonomic group that cannot be defined by a single character. Indeed, none of the above mentioned features satisfactorily diagnose the genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B78CB7FBD71ECC802EBFB44FD27" author="Schmalfuss" box="[996,1198,646,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" refString="Schmalfuss, H. (1992) The terrestrial isopod genus Porcellio in western Asia (Oniscidea: Porcellionidae). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A, 475, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="1992">Schmalfuss 1992</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B78CB7FBD71EBE902EBFA76FD27" author="Schmalfuss" box="[1221,1436,646,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" refString="Schmalfuss, H. (1998) The terrestrial isopod fauna of the central Near East countries: Composition and biogeography. Israel Journal of Zoology, 44, 263 - 271." type="journal article" year="1998">Schmalfuss (1998)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D0ACB7FBD71EE3302C7FE6CFD7B" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[287,390,682,707]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EE3302C7FE6CFD7B" box="[287,390,682,707]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Porcellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a paraphyletic group including two different linages that have been united due to convergent evolution. According to him, “the north African 
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EC1902A3FBCEFD5F" box="[821,1060,718,743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">laevis-hoffmannseggi</emphasis>
-group defined by elongated male pleopod exopodites, probably should be considered a separate genus which then must be called 
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EBF30299FAABFCB3" box="[1247,1345,756,779]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Rogopus</emphasis>
Budde- Lund, 1908”. The northern Mediterranean 
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71ED52037BFCD7FC97" box="[638,829,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">scaber-obsolotus</emphasis>
-group is diagnosed by short pleopod exopodites that includes also west Asian species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B78CB7FBD71ED380357FD30FCEB" author="Schmalfuss" box="[532,730,826,851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" refString="Schmalfuss, H. (1992) The terrestrial isopod genus Porcellio in western Asia (Oniscidea: Porcellionidae). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A, 475, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="1992">Schmalfuss 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Obviously, a revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D0ACB7FBD71EB5A0357FB37FCEB" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[1142,1245,826,851]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EA9BCB7FBD71EB5A0357FB37FCEB" box="[1142,1245,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Porcellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is required to be divided to more natural genera.
</paragraph>
